    <h2>Donor and Recipient Questions</h2>
    <h3>Q: How can I donate blood?</h3>
    <p>A: You can donate blood by visiting our clinical office or the recipient can contact you, and you can donate to him, but in either case, you must acknowledge us for record purposes. In most cases, donors can donate whole blood every 8 to 12 weeks. Please check with your local blood bank for specific guidelines.</p>

    <h3>Q: How much units can a donor donate?</h3>
    <p>A: Maximum 3 in a month</p>
    <h3>Q: How much units of blood can a recipient receive?</h3>
    <p>A: Maximum 1 in a month</p>
    <h3>Q: Is blood donation safe?</h3>
    <p>A: Yes, blood donation is a safe and well-regulated process. All equipment used is sterile and disposable, and trained professionals handle the entire donation process. Donors are encouraged to follow post-donation guidelines to ensure their well-being.</p>

